Anterior gonopod
sternite basally wide, apically elevated into a lobe with a triangular, well-rounded tip (
Fig. 26I
). Sternite tip almost as high as mesal process of coxite; latter relatively slender, elongated, longer than sternite (
Fig. 26I
). Telopodite on posterior side apically with a large triangular, retrorse process (
Fig. 26K
). Process projecting above coxite and telopodite (
Fig. 26K
).

Posterior gonopods
telopodite laterally with a single, large, finger-shaped process (
Fig. 26J, x
). Second small projection, where sperm canal is discharging, is located close to apex (
Fig. 26M, y
). A large, bi-lobical membrane present apically. Membrane apically three times wider than basally (
Fig. 26L, z
). A small, white, swollen area (
Fig. 26M
) is also located basally of membrane.
